</b></p>
<p>128.34.<b> Engage in a constructive cooperation with United Nations special 
procedures (Slovakia); 
</b></p>
<p>128.35.<b> Accept to adhere its human rights record to the examination of the 
human rights experts and the relevant bodies and other United Nations 
</b></p>
<p><b>mechanisms on the same manner of all members of the United Nations and in 
</b></p>
<p><b>accordance with the existing rules and regulations (Sudan); 
</b></p>
<p>128.36.<b> Organize visits to Canada of the Special Rapporteur on the human 
rights of migrants, the Special Rapporteur on torture, the Special Rapporteur 
</b></p>
<p><b>on extrajudicial executions, the Special Rapporteur on trafficking in persons, 
</b></p>
<p><b>especially women and children and the Special Rapporteur on sale of children, 
</b></p>
<p><b>child prostitution and child pornography (Belarus);</b> 
</p>
<p>128.37. <b>Renew its commitment in favour of a national strategy to fight 
against racism (Togo); 
</b></p>
<p>128.38.<b> Continue its efforts to combat racial discrimination (Gabon); 
